        <li><a href="index.html#contact">Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
      <a class="btn-idioma" href="../instructores.html">ES</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <header class="caso-hero">
    <div class="contenedor">
      <p class="caso-cejilla">Case study · Internal instructor training</p>
      <h1>Two programs, one conviction</h1>
      <p class="caso-tesis">
        That an organization's knowledge shouldn't depend on a single person — that's
        the promise of a good internal instructor program. In global manufacturing I
        learned it by rescuing a program that was slowly dying. In the tequila industry
        I applied it by building one from my own pedagogical judgment.
      </p>
      <div class="meta-caso">
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-etiqueta">Industries</span>
          <span class="meta-valor">Global manufacturing · Tequila industry</span>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-etiqueta">My role</span>
          <span class="meta-valor">Instructional design · Program management · Facilitation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <span class="meta-etiqueta">Scope</span>
          <span class="meta-valor">100+ instructors trained · Program documented institutionally</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="capitulo">
    <div class="contenedor">
      <p class="capitulo-numero">Chapter 1 · Global manufacturing</p>
      <h2>From a fading program to an institutional project</h2>
      <div class="timeline" id="timeline-1"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="capitulo fondo-suave">
    <div class="contenedor">
      <p class="capitulo-numero">Chapter 2 · Tequila industry</p>
      <h2>Design from scratch, adapt without giving in</h2>
      <div class="timeline" id="timeline-2"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cierre">
    <div class="contenedor">
      <h2 class="titulo-seccion">What I learned crossing both worlds</h2>
      <hr class="linea">
      <div class="cierre-grid">
        <div class="cierre-tarjeta">
          <p class="cejilla-mini">Global manufacturing</p>
          <p>A program without a clear owner fades, no matter how good the original idea was. Traceability, leadership sponsorship, and defined roles aren't bureaucracy — they're what keeps a project alive.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cierre-tarjeta">
          <p class="cejilla-mini">Tequila industry</p>
          <p>When operations ask for less, the answer isn't to give in — it's to redesign. The time constraint was what pushed me to make better use of available resources and apply a methodology that turned out to be more effective than the original format.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="cierre-reflexion">
        In both contexts, the internal instructor role doesn't sustain itself. It needs
        design, accompaniment, feedback, and a standard to aspire to. My work in both
        cases was to build that standard — and make sure it was documented to outlast
        my own tenure.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="nav-casos">
